			<h2 class="featurette-heading">Anna</h2>
			<p>Anna is one of nine children and when she is not at school she spends her time reading or taking care of her younger brothers. Part of the reason she wants to go to secondary school is so that she can get a good job and help pay the school fees of those younger brothers. Anna's mother is a community health worker (a volunteer position) and Anna is close to her. He mother supports Anna going to secondary school and wrote the following unsolicited letter:</p><br><p>Dear sir/madam,</p>
			<p>RE: Application for sponsorship at secondary school</p>
<p>With reference to the above subject, I write to ask for the sponsorship of my child
from grade 10 to 12. Her names are Anastasia Kunda and she is currently in grade
9 at Ng’answa Primary School. She is 16 years old and the third born in the
	family of 9.</p>
<p>Her elder siblings did not manage to complete school because I did not manage to
pay for them. That is the reason why I am asking for sponsorship for this one. Her
father and I are not working and have no means of sponsoring this child.
	Your consideration in this respect will be highly appreciated.</p>
			<p>Yours faithfully,</p>
<p>Anastasia Chibengele</p>
